{
  "texts": [
    "Their works primarily focus on modifying model structures, devising encoding methods, and designing training objectives to tailor the models for table tasks.",
    "For example, TaPas [8] extends BERT's [61] model architecture and mask language modeling objective to pre-train and fine-tune with tables and related text segments.",
    "TaBERT [7] encodes a subset of table content most relevant to the input utterance and employs a vertical attention mechanism.",
    "TURL [9] encodes information of table components (e.g., caption, headers, and cells) into separate input embeddings and fuses them together.",
    "TABBIE [62] modifies the training objective to detect corrupted cells."
  ]
}